OL,6,FShe said: "Since I was appointed as a
OL,7,Fbereavement midwife in 1998, I have
OL,8,Fcampaigned for a standardised care
OL,9,Fpathway that ensures that every parent
OL,10,Fexperiencing baby loss ` regardless of
OL,11,Fthe gestation or type of loss `
OL,12,Freceives the physical and emotional
OL,13,Fcare and support they deserve.
OL,15,F"Removing the restrictions around the
OL,16,Fapplication process will give all
OL,17,Fbereaved parents of pre-24 week baby
OL,18,Floss the official recognition that
OL,19,Ftheir babies did exist and that their
OL,20,Fbabies' lives, however brief, really
OL,21,Fdo matter."
